snippet.textDisplay:
It should be pointed out that the Blue Origin "New Shepard" used liquid Oxygen and Liquid Hydrogen as fuel so the exhaust was just steam/water vapour, However the Virgin Galatic attempt used solid carbon-based fuel, hydroxyl-terminated polybutadiene (HTPB), The exhausat from this produces CO2, soot and some water vapor. The nitrogen-based oxidant used by VSS Unity also generates nitrogen oxides.

So moving forwards I hope more people copy the New Shepard fuels but maybe not the unfortunate shape.

snippet.textDisplay: Almost had my 3060 fried after starting AC VALHALLA the other day. It was immediately after a bunch of Ubisoft client updates, not sure if that had anything to do with it. If I hadn't immediately jumped to thermal throttle tanking my fps my card would be fucked right now.
